Open bug `microtasks-starved-by-pending-timer` (NOTES.md).  Even with a
`setTimeout(0)`, the microtask queued by `Promise.resolve().then()` does
not drain before the timer fires.  This is a stronger statement than the
existing regression-microtask-not-starved test (which used a pending
100ms timer) — the bug shows up at the absolute minimum timer too.

Anomaly: `await-resumes-as-microtask` (same .js dir) PASSES.  The async
IIFE + await path apparently yields to microtasks while a bare
`Promise.resolve().then()` does not.  Worth investigating when the
microtask checkpoint pump work lands.
